Document: OpenXRSpatialEntityExtension
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrspatialentityextension.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for managing spatial entities, contexts, and snapshots within the OpenXR environment.

Method: add_spatial_entity(spatial_context: RID, entity_id: int, entity: int) → RID
Registers an entity that was created directly on the OpenXR runtime.

Method: create_spatial_context(capability_configurations: Array[OpenXRSpatialCapabilityConfigurationBaseHeader], next: OpenXRStructureBase = null, user_callback: Callable = Callable()) → OpenXRFutureResult
Creates a new spatial context that handles entities for the provided capability configurations. capability_configurations is an array of OpenXRSpatialCapabilityConfigurationBaseHeader with the needed capability configuration data. next is an optional parameter that can contain additional information for creating our spatial context. Note: This is an asynchronous method and returns an OpenXRFutureResult object with which to track the status, discarding this object will not cancel the creation process. On success user_callback will be called if specified. The result data for this function is the RID for our spatial context.

Method: discover_spatial_entities(spatial_context: RID, component_types: PackedInt64Array, next: OpenXRStructureBase = null, user_callback: Callable = Callable()) → OpenXRFutureResult
Starts a new discovery query, this will gather all objects tracked by the spatial_context that have at least one of the component types specified in component_types. next is an optional parameter that can contain additional information for executing the discovery query. Note: This is an asynchronous method and returns an OpenXRFutureResult object with which to track the status, discarding this object will not cancel the discovery process. On success user_callback will be called if specified. The result data for this function is the RID for our snapshot.

Method: find_spatial_entity(entity_id: int) → RID
Returns the RID for the specified spatial entity ID.

Method: free_spatial_context(spatial_context: RID) → void
Frees a spatial context previously created when calling create_spatial_context(). If the spatial context creation is still ongoing, the asynchronous process is cancelled.

Method: free_spatial_entity(entity: RID) → void
Frees an entity previously created when calling add_spatial_entity() or make_spatial_entity().

Method: free_spatial_snapshot(spatial_snapshot: RID) → void
Frees a spatial snapshot previously created when calling discover_spatial_entities(). If the spatial snapshot creation is still ongoing, the asynchronous process is cancelled.

Method: get_float_buffer(spatial_snapshot: RID, buffer_id: int) const → PackedFloat32Array
Returns a buffer with floats from a buffer that was retrieved when taking a snapshot.

Method: get_spatial_context_handle(spatial_context: RID) const → int
Returns the OpenXR spatial context handle for this snapshot. Note: This method is intended to be used from GDExtensions that implement spatial entity capability handlers.

Method: get_spatial_context_ready(spatial_context: RID) const → bool
Returns true if the spatial context finished its creation and is ready to be used.

Method: get_spatial_entity_context(entity: RID) const → RID
Returns the spatial context for this entity.

Method: get_spatial_entity_id(entity: RID) const → int
Returns the internal XrSpatialEntityIdEXT associated with the entity.

Method: get_spatial_snapshot_context(spatial_snapshot: RID) const → RID
Returns the spatial context related to this spatial snapshot.

Method: get_spatial_snapshot_handle(spatial_snapshot: RID) const → int
Returns the OpenXR spatial snapshot handle for this snapshot. Note: This method is intended to be used from GDExtensions that implement spatial entity capability handlers.

Method: get_string(spatial_snapshot: RID, buffer_id: int) const → String
Returns a string from a buffer that was retrieved when taking a snapshot.